html:tr.html:td:
A morphism (A,m)  \to  (B,n) is a morphism f \colon  A  \to  B in \mathcal { C } such that m is a pullback against n along f. In other words, m is isomorphic to the canonical pullback f ^{*} (n) in \mathsf { Sub } (A).





