       \DiagramSquare {
        width = 3cm,
        nw = (hg)f,
        ne = h(gf),
        sw = {(h'g')f'},
        se = {h'(g'f')},
        north = {a_{h,g,f}},
        south = {a_{h',g',f'}},
        west = {( \gamma  *  \beta ) *  \alpha },
        east = { \gamma  * ( \beta  *  \alpha )},
      }

Naturality of the unitors: For any 2-cell \alpha \colon f \to f', the following squares commute.





