     \DiagramSquare {
      nw = { { \mathopen {} \llbracket \Gamma . \varphi \rrbracket \mathclose {}} _{ M } },
      ne = {M( \Gamma )},
      sw = { { \mathopen {} \llbracket \Gamma . \varphi \rrbracket \mathclose {}} _{ N } },
      se = {N( \Gamma )},
      north/style = {>->},
      south/style = {>->},
      east = {h_{ \Gamma }},
      west = g,
    }



  Here, h_{ \Gamma } is a shorthand for h_{A_{1}}  \times   \cdots   \times  h_{A_{n}}, where A_{1}, \ldots ,A_{n} are sorts appearing in the context \Gamma.

  If R  \rightarrowtail  A_{1}, \ldots ,A_{n} is a relation symbol and t_{1}, \ldots ,t_{n} are terms of appropriate sorts, then { \mathopen {} \llbracket \Gamma .R(t_{1}, \ldots ,t_{n}) \rrbracket \mathclose {}} _{ M } is the following pullback:





