    Let M and N be \Sigma-structures.
    A homomorphism h \colon M \to N consists of an indexed family of morphisms h_{A} \colon MA \to NA for each sort A.
    This data is subject to the following conditions:


        For each function symbol f \colon A_{1}, \ldots ,A_{n} \to B, the following square commutes:





