where \varepsilon is the counit defined on the right. Then naturality is a consequence of uniqueness.

Let g  \in   {{ \mathcal { C } }_{/{ B }}} be an object. We take \varepsilon _{g} \colon \Sigma _{f}( f ^{*} (g)) \to g to be the following morphism.





   \RequirePackage {tikz}
   \RequirePackage {amsmath}
   \usetikzlibrary {backgrounds, intersections, calc, spath3, fit}

   \definecolor {catccolor}{RGB}{255,244,138}
   \tikzstyle {dot}=[circle, draw=black, fill=black, minimum size=1mm, inner sep=0mm]
   \tikzstyle {catc}=[catccolor!60]
